UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2533
1 A RESOLUTION adjourning the Senate in honor of the life and legacy of Brigadier
2 General Billy Brandon Morgan.
3 WHEREAS, Brigadier General Billy Brandon Morgan was born on April 11, 1929,
4 in Puryear, Tennessee, and was raised in Benton, Kentucky, where he graduated from
5 Benton High School in 1947; and
6 WHEREAS, he pursued higher education at Freed-Hardeman College before
7 transferring to Murray State University, where he earned a degree in business in 1950;
8 and
9 WHEREAS, in 1951, he enlisted in the United States Air Force and was accepted
10 into the Aviation Cadet Pilot Training Program, beginning a distinguished military career
11 marked by dedication, professionalism, and service to the nation, and
12 WHEREAS, Brigadier General Billy Brandon Morgan served as pilot instructor and
13 pilot in Germany and France during and after the Korean War, where he met and married
14 his sweetheart, Irene Whiteside, of Texas, and
15 WHEREAS, while stationed in Lubbock, Texas, he served as associate professor of
16 air science and commandant of cadets at Texas Tech University, where he earned a
17 Master of Arts degree in Government, and
18 WHEREAS, after returning to Benton in 1960, Brigadier General Billy Brandon
19 Morgan continued his service in the United States Air Force Reserve and the Tennessee
20 Air National Guard, flying troop and cargo missions during the Vietnam War; and
21 WHEREAS, Brigadier General Billy Brandon Morgan ultimately achieved the rank
22 of brigadier general in 1981, and retired in September 1985 after 35 years of honorable
23 active, reserve, and Air National Guard service, and
24 WHEREAS, throughout his military career he received numerous decorations and
25 commendations, including the Legion of Merit, Meritorious Service Medal, National
26 Defense Service Medal, Army of Occupation Medal (Germany), Commendation Ribbon,
27 Armed Forces Longevity Service Award, and Air Force Outstanding Unit Award; and
Page 1 of 4
