UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2533
1 WHEREAS, Brigadier General Billy Brandon Morgan was a lifelong member of
2 the Benton Church of Christ, faithfully serving as a deacon for 25 years and as an elder
3 for 20 years, and
4 WHEREAS, he was a founding supporter of the West Kentucky Children's Home,
5 now known as New Pathways for Children, and served for more than three decades on
6 the board of directors of the French African Christian Education in Benin, West Africa;
7 and
8 WHEREAS, Brigadier General Billy Brandon Morgan was a respected community
9 leader and businessman in Benton, Kentucky, serving as a principal owner, independent
10 insurance agent, and realtor with Morgan, Trevathan, and Gunn for 35 years; and
11 WHEREAS, he served his community in numerous leadership roles, including the
12 Benton City Council, the Benton Lions Club, the Marshall County Chamber of
13 Commerce, the Kentucky-Barkley Lake Board of Realtors, the Marshall County Hospital
14 Board of Directors, and as a founder and director of the Marshall County High School
15 Athletic Foundation. He also served as chairman of the board of directors for Bradshaw
16 & Weil, Inc., as a director for several banks in western Kentucky, and was named to the
17 Marshall County Schools Distinguished Hall of Fame; and
18 WHEREAS, Brigadier General Billy Brandon Morgan was a devoted supporter of
19 higher education, serving as chairman and longtime member of the board of trustees for
20 Freed-Hardeman University, where he was recognized as an Outstanding Alumnus and
21 received an honorary Doctor of Laws degree; and
22 WHEREAS, he was inducted into the Freed-Hardeman University Sports Hall of
23 Fame and the Tennessee Independent Colleges and Universities Association Hall of
24 Fame; and
25 WHEREAS, he was a lifetime member of the Murray State University Alumni
26 Association, served on the Murray State University Board of Regents, and received the
27 Distinguished Alumnus Award for Professional Achievement and the Golden Horseshoe
Page 2 of 4
XXXX 3/5/2026 12:53 PM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2533
1 Award for volunteer service to the university; and
2 WHEREAS, Brigadier General Billy Brandon Morgan was a devoted husband,
3 father, and family man who cherished time spent with his loved ones and enjoyed sharing
4 his passion for sports, whether cheering on his favorite teams or encouraging friendly
5 competition, using those moments to pass on lessons of teamwork, perseverance, and
6 character that will continue to guide those who knew and loved him, and
7 WHEREAS, Brigadier General Billy Brandon Morgan passed away peacefully on
8 February 28, 2026, at the age of 96, surrounded by his family, and
9 WHEREAS, he was preceded in death by his beloved wife of 60 years, Irene
10 Whiteside Morgan, and is survived by his daughter, Shannon Morgan (Daniel) West; his
11 son, Brandon W. (Janet) Morgan; his sisters, Patricia Hodges and Martha Kaye Lincoln;
12 his brother, Phillip Morgan; four grandchildren, ten great-grandchildren, and many nieces
13 and nephews; and
14 WHEREAS, Brigadier General Billy Brandon Morgan was known for his wit,
15 wisdom, generosity, and devotion to family, faith, and community. He leaves behind a
16 legacy that will continue to inspire the people of Marshall County and the
17 Commonwealth of the Kentucky;
18 NOW, THEREFORE,
19 Be it resolved by the Senate of the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of
20 Kentucky:
21 Section 1. The Senate honors the life, service, and legacy of Brigadier General
22 Billy Brandon Morgan and recognizes his extraordinary contributions to the United
23 States of America, the Commonwealth of Kentucky, and the community of Benton,
24 Kentucky.
25 Section 2. When the Senate adjourns this day, it does so in honor and loving
26 memory of Brigadier General Billy Brandon Morgan.
27 Section 3. The Clerk of the Senate is directed to transmit a copy of this
